The short run equilibrium price of widgets is the price that equates the industry supply function with the demand function. Thus, we need to solve the equation $100 p^{\frac{1}{2}}=6400 / p^{\frac{1}{2}}$ for $p$.
\begin{align*}
100 p^{\frac{1}{2}}&=6400 / p^{\frac{1}{2}}\\
\Rightarrow\qquad 100 p&=6400\\
\Rightarrow\qquad p&=64
\end{align*}
The short run equilibrium price of widgets is $p=64$.

